title: The Quantum Tapes
description: In 2017, I dropped my first track called Space-time, which followed the scientific discovery of time travel in the year 2044. This tale was centered around a character known as Dr. Haven and this mixtape is a continuation of his story. After working late one night in his photonics research laboratory, he had a dream that led to the discovery of tachyon particles, which can theoretically travel through time. After making the decision to go back to the past and right his wrongs, he stumbles upon three versions of his own reality, each teaching him a lesson in letting go and growing as a person. This forces our main protagonist to realize that no matter how far back you travel, sometimes we simply need to move forward to find peace within ourselves.\n\nMixtape Cover Photo Credit: Evan Tvrdik

title: YUMO - BEDITATION E.P (3615001)
description:
XXXVI.XV and L\INCONNU present "REC¬∞ S√©ries"
3615001 YUMO - BEDITATION E.P
Out on June 17th.

Youngunz R.I.P

These new projects undertaken by our artists, and the closing of our management and booking services present us now with the opportunity to move on the next one : XXXVI.XV (3615 - a little nod to our dear Minitel French lover!) This structure, starting off as digital only, will allow us to further explore the international scene and to have a more intense rhythm of release. Being the types who never appreciate a premature evacuation from our night time activities, the idea of the label is to put together a comprehensive image of our artists erotic visions and past-times! The end of the night is always for us to decide, and therefore we hope that these artists will provide the perfect soundtrack to your long nights out, and our even longer mornings in. EPs consist of a maximum of four tracks and no remixes. It‚Äôs a strict and controlled remit for the artists. A short, and condensed sonic representation of carnal desire, tender love or just a quiet shared sensual moment.

For these first three releases, the label will be collaborating with the birthplace of the idea, L\INCONNU, through the ‚ÄúREC‚Äù series. XXXVI.XV and L\INCONNU aim to distill the soundtrack to your night. As the doors to the bars and clubs close, so new more intimate doors open!
